{"type":"message","id":"2653f5a0","parentId":"a3c53d74","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:03:13.305Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5vgv6oisirve_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 005914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a specific action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n- The big insight is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action from the goals is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nFor this pulse, I should take ONE concrete action that advances the TIC experiment. The most logical first step is to:\r\n1. Read the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md to understand the TIC algorithm\r\n2. Create an initial TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and create a concrete action. I should:\r\n1. Read the research doc to understand the TIC approach\r\n2. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nActually, since I'm stateless and need to work with files, I should:\r\n1. Read the research doc (COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md) \r\n2. Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n\r\nLet me be concrete and specific. I'll create the TIC experiment script that:\r\n- Loads the pulse logs\r\n- Implements invariant/variant classification\r\n- Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to see what exists. Let me write an action to create the TIC experiment code.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action: Create `experiments/tic_classifier.py` that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLet me write this as a concrete file edit - creating the TIC experiment implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1 advancement. I need to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure = invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation that will:\r\n1. Load pulse logs and extract temporal patterns\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (causal) vs variant (epiphenomenal)\r\n3. Test next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nEXPERIMENT_DIR = Path(\"experiments/tic_results\")\r\nEXPERIMENT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n]\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for log in reversed(logs):  # chronological order\r\n        content = log.read_text()\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': log.name,\r\n            'content': content,\r\n            'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n        })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features for invariance detection.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        'goals_mentioned': [],\r\n        'insights': [],\r\n        'pending_items': [],\r\n        'file_refs': [],\r\n        'concepts': []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Track goal references\r\n    goal_pattern = r'## (Active|Pending|Completed)'\r\n    features['goals_mentioned'] = re.findall(goal_pattern, pulse['content'])\r\n    \r\n    # Track insight markers\r\n    insight_pattern = r'\\*\\*[^*]+\\*\\*'\r\n    features['insights'] = re.findall(insight_pattern, pulse['content'])\r\n    \r\n    # Track file references\r\n    file_pattern = r'`([\\w/._-]+\\.\\w+)`'\r\n    features['file_refs'] = re.findall(file_pattern, pulse['content'])\r\n    \r\n    # Track concept keywords\r\n    concept_keywords = ['compression', 'causal', 'invariant', 'temporal', \r\n                        'λ', 'decay', 'gap', 'pulse', 'memory', 'architecture']\r\n    text_lower = pulse['content'].lower()\r\n    features['concepts'] = [k for k in concept_keywords if k in text_lower]\r\n    \r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(feature_history):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute invariance score based on persistence across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if not feature_history:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    scores = []\r\n    for feature_type in ['goals_mentioned', 'insights', 'file_refs', 'concepts']:\r\n        history = feature_history.get(feature_type, [])\r\n        if len(history) >= 2:\r\n            # Invariant if appears in >70% of recent pulses\r\n            persistence = sum(history) / len(history)\r\n            scores.append(persistence)\r\n    \r\n    return sum(scores) / len(scores) if scores else 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_variant(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant (causal) or variant (epiphenomenal).\"\"\"\r\n    results = []\r\n    \r\n    # Build feature history\r\n    feature_history = defaultdict(list)\r\n    all_features = []\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        features = extract_features(pulse)\r\n        all_features.append(features)\r\n        \r\n        for ftype, items in features.items():\r\n            feature_history[ftype].append(len(items))\r\n    \r\n    # Classify each pulse\r\n    for i, (pulse, features) in\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:59:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328593294}}
